CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 16, 1966, pg. 1B reads: "Discussing Goldfish - Mrs. Geri Hart (seated) former Pittsburgher now residing in Washington, D.C., is seen discussing the varieties of goldfish found in the indoor pond at the Holiday House, with Mrs. Gerald H. Tames. Mrs. Hart is an active member of the well-known Pittsburgher Club of Washington."
TitMainTitle: Geri Hart and Mrs. Gerald H. Tames, looking at goldfish in decorative pool in the Holiday House for Squaws "Cotton Extravaganza" Dinner-Dance, Monroeville
